description:
Open for recipe 👇

This haystacks recipe is a no-fuss layered salad that’s a complete meal in itself. Seasoned lentils, lettuce, chopped veggies, and ranch dressing come together in a savoury haystack style. Enjoy this hearty vegan salad for breakfast to power you through your day. Or layer it in a mason jar for a packable lunch.  Use canned lentils to make this lentil salad faster. See how it’s done!

Lentil Haystacks
Prepare lentils:
2 c dry lentils
5 c water
½ c onion, chopped
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 ½ tsp salt
1 tbsp onion powder
1 tsp paprika
2 c tomatoes, diced

Toppings:
Green leaf lettuce
½ c onion, diced
1 each yellow and orange peppers, diced
2 tomatoes, chopped
1 avocado, diced
1 bunch green onions, chopped
1 c olives, chopped
Vegan ranch dressing

Vegan, gluten free, soy free (if using soy free dressing), dairy free.
